  "analysis": "The 10:1 imbalance reflects natural benthic distributions but risks high false-negative rates for mortality events. The strategy focuses on upsampling the 'Dead Scallop' class to a 2:1 ratio (250 annotations) to stabilize the loss function and improve feature extraction for 'clapper' shells without over-fitting, while maintaining the 'Live Scallop' count to preserve existing variance.",
  "classes": [
