      "class_name": "Live Scallop",
      "current_count": 500,
      "target_count": 500,
      "strategy": "keep",
      "rationale": "500 annotations provide a sufficient baseline for fine-tuning on a majority class. Keeping this count avoids unnecessary data synthesis while maintaining the model's exposure to the natural variety of live scallop poses and seafloor backgrounds."
    },
    {
      "class_name": "Dead Scallop",
      "current_count": 50,
      "target_count": 250,
      "strategy": "upsample",
      "rationale": "50 samples are insufficient for the model to distinguish subtle features of dead scallops (e.g., gaping shells or empty valves) across different lighting and turbidity. Upsampling to 250 creates a 2:1 ratio that prioritizes minority class recall, which is critical for accurate mortality rate estimation in fisheries surveys."
    }
  ]
}

